warlock":{"—":"—","Blunt":"Blunt","Bow":"Bow","Brawling":"Brawling","Crossbow":"Crossbow","Large blade":"Large blade","Pole arm":"Pole arm","Small blade":"Small blade","Thrown":"Thrown"},"warpstar":{"—":"—","Blades":"Blades","Blunt":"Blunt","Brawling":"Brawling","Ship gunner":"Ship gunner","Small arms":"Small arms","Thrown":"Thrown"}}},"activeSystem":"warlock"},"ownership":{"default":0,"HcHB4gb18gtp2Q2n":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"DVdRVhG5AjQpEUgr","name":"Hide","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"","choices":{"":"","Light":"Light","Modest":"Modest","Heavy":"Heavy"}},"reductionRoll":"1d3"},"ownership":{"default":0,"HcHB4gb18gtp2Q2n":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"zyI0aur2aicgT6LR","name":"Intelligent","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":700000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.viEhV1k2WBxXnAHV"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This being is intelligent, can speak (but perhaps not in a tongue the characters know) and use tools and weapons. It is also able to create strategies and plans.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"WjT7h1CDjuYk9PMW","name":"Spell caster","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":750000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FOVCFt6tZfXWVBEK"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The being is able to cast spells. The games master should feel free to assign the creature spells that reflect its power. It uses stamina to cast spells and requires an incantation skill check.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RuSxoPyrInzMdmNe","name":"Poisonous","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":725000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.56fsf7S8NIppsAj2"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This creature carries a poison or can inject a venom. If it successfully hits a target, the victim must test their luck. If they fail, the victim is poisoned, and loses [[/roll 1d6]] stamina at the start of the next [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. Poison or venom effects from the same source are not cumulative, although of course the creature can still inflict its normal damage when it hits.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"CblQrSjDC8H449uj","name":"Flying","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":500000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2RsIqNmhzsx9vw6I"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Using wings or similar, this creature can fly. Treat this as normal movement, but ignoring barriers that can be flown over at the game master's discretion. This creature cannot be engaged in melee combat whilst flying unless it chooses to attack, in which case it can be targeted.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warlock.8hTjuMvIDr7IRKjk"}},"system":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":3,"max":3},"stamina":{"value":40,"max":40}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Another magical creation, the manticore resembles a lion with the face of a man, huge bat wings and the tail of a scorpion. They are prodigious spell casters, and acquisition of magical items drives them. Some theorise that a sorcerer created them long ago to seek out items of power.</p>"},"type":"Monster","weaponSkill":9,"adventuringSkills":7,"gear":{"weapons":[],"armour":[],"equipment":[]}},"ownership":{"default":0,"HcHB4gb18gtp2Q2n":3},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Manticore","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":360,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false,"type":null},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1},"attenuation":0.5,"color":null},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"texture":{"src":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/griffin-symbol.svg","scaleX":1,"scaleY":1,"offsetX":0,"offsetY":0,"rotation":0,"tint":null},"sight":{"angle":360,"enabled":false,"range":0,"brightness":1,"color":null,"attenuation":0.1,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"visionMode":"basic"},"detectionModes":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"warlock","systemVersion":"2.0.0","coreVersion":"10.284","createdTime":1662145221517,"modifiedTime":1662412744005,"lastModifiedBy":"6R9Y3cM97XtOXeBn"}}
{"_id":"9nVYNO0fj8RL86ht","name":"Human","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"VHGfsXeCUJT7DQ2i","name":"Intelligent","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":700000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.viEhV1k2WBxXnAHV"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This being is intelligent, can speak (but perhaps not in a tongue the characters know) and use tools and weapons. It is also able to create strategies and plans.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warlock.9nVYNO0fj8RL86ht"}},"system":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":15,"max":15}},"biography":{"description":"<p>In the Kingdom there are many humans, whose desire to congregate makes them very populous. Many of these people have never strayed far from their homes, and apart from the odd elf, dwarf or halfling have never seen some of the other races that inhabit the Kingdom and the surrounding lands.</p>"},"type":"Civilised","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":5,"gear":{"weapons":[],"armour":[],"equipment":[]}},"ownership":{"default":0,"HcHB4gb18gtp2Q2n":3},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Human","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":360,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false,"type":null},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1},"attenuation":0.5,"color":null},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"texture":{"src":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/character.svg","scaleX":1,"scaleY":1,"offsetX":0,"offsetY":0,"rotation":0,"tint":null},"sight":{"angle":360,"enabled":false,"range":0,"brightness":1,"color":null,"attenuation":0.1,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"visionMode":"basic"},"detectionModes":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"warlock","systemVersion":"2.0.0","coreVersion":"10.284","createdTime":1662145221520,"modifiedTime":1662412744005,"lastModifiedBy":"6R9Y3cM97XtOXeBn"}}
{"_id":"Cx9g6UFY947kk07F","name":"Ratman","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/rat.svg","items":[{"_id":"2MhN8B7o0QucXpFP","name":"Intelligent","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":"jZ1bx1OgshF0koNu","sort":700000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.viEhV1k2WBxXnAHV"}},"system":{"description":"<p>This being is intelligent, can speak (but perhaps not in a tongue the characters know) and use tools and weapons. It is also able to create strategies and plans.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"_stats":{"systemId":null,"systemVersion":null,"coreVersion":null,"createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":null,"lastModifiedBy":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warlock.Cx9g6UFY947kk07F"}},"system":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":10,"max":10}},"biography":{"description":"<p>In the cities of the Kingdom, many simply believe these filthy creatures don't exist. The wise know better. Ratmen infest the sewers and cellars of many towns, and form their own courts and kingdoms in a mockery of what lies above. They are intelligent and can talk, but their high pitched squeaky voices are hard to understand.</p>"},"type":"Uncivilised","weaponSkill":4,"adventuringSkills":3,"gear":{"weapons":[],"armour":[],"equipment":[]}},"ownership":{"default":0,"HcHB4gb18gtp2Q2n":3},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Ratman","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":360,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false,"type":null},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1},"attenuation":0.5,"color":null},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"texture":{"src":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/rat.svg","